Coupling OpenFOAM with external simulation codes using OpenFOAM-preCICE
SCCS, TUM School of Computation, Information and Technology
OpenFOAM-preCICE: Coupling OpenFOAM with external solvers for multi-physics simulations
[2] G. Chourdakis, K. Davis, B. Rodenberg, M. Schulte, F. Simonis, B. Uekermann, et al. (2022),
preCICE v2: A sustainable and user-friendly coupling library [version 2; peer review: 2 approved]
All figures originate from the OpenFOAM-preCICE paper [1].
Users of simulation codes often wish to
solved in OpenFOAM. Such problems appear
in cooling devices, on flexible wings, or even
in nuclear fusion reactors. The OpenFOAM-
preCICE adapter allows users to quickly
couple OpenFOAM to arbitrary other codes,
bridging their communities, and opening new
P2P (without a server): MUI, OpenPALM, preCICE
